The famous Unix and Dos consoles are still favourites, if you need to use a lot of commands and you remember them. They are all what I call _one click_ commands, you do not need to navigate to get to where you want and then click. You just type the command. This is also my petty theory as to why hackers, that they would normally embrace new technology, refuse to give up the console. I also made similar observations with CAD Operators that still prefer AUTOCAD's command line to using the menus.  Beyond other advantages of consoles is also that you have a very quick response. In most cases almost instantaneous feedback.


